verses.text_plain: The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand, until I make thine enemies thy footstool.
verses.verse_html: 1The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou at my right hand, until I make thine enemies thy footstool.

verses.text_plain: The Lord shall send the rod of thy strength out of Zion: rule thou in the midst of thine enemies.
verses.verse_html: 2The Lord shall send the rod of thy strength out of Zion: rule thou in the midst of thine enemies.

verses.text_plain: Thy people shall be willing in the day of thy power, in the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning: thou hast the dew of thy youth.
verses.verse_html:
3Thy people shall be willing in the day of thy power, in the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning: thou hast the dew of thy youth. ▼
▼ from…: or, more than the womb of the morning: thou shalt have, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ from…: or, more than the womb of the morning: thou shalt have, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ from…: or, more than the womb of the morning: thou shalt have, etc

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath sworn, and will not repent, Thou art a priest for ever after the order of Melchizedek.
verses.verse_html: 4The Lord hath sworn, and will not repent, Thou art a priest for ever after the order of Melchizedek.

verses.text_plain: The Lord at thy right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath.
verses.verse_html: 5The Lord at thy right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath.

verses.text_plain: He shall judge among the heathen, he shall fill the places with the dead bodies; he shall wound the heads over many countries.
verses.verse_html:
6He shall judge among the heathen, he shall fill the places with the dead bodies; he shall wound the heads over many countries. ▼
▼ many: or, great

verses.text_plain: He shall drink of the brook in the way: therefore shall he lift up the head.
verses.verse_html: 7He shall drink of the brook in the way: therefore shall he lift up the head.
